<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-08-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-08-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="109" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d109">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 825.00/69.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Chilean
                                Chargé</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-08-18"><hi rend="italic">August 18,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 39.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your No. 18 of the 11th instant, with which you inclose, for
                            transmission to the President of the United States, a letter addressed
                            to him by the President of Chile. You express the thanks of the
                            President of Chile for the courtesies accorded him on the occasion of
                            his visit to the United States.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to inform you that the letter of the President of Chile
                            has been forwarded to the President of the United States in accord with
                            your request.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington
                            Wilson</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>